Package com.googlecode.cqengine.query.simple

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FilterQuery<O,A>
    Extracting a value from an object via an Attribute can sometimes be expensive, for example if the attribute is virtual wherein the data it reads is not already stored in memory, but has to be uncompressed or decoded on-the-fly, or if it reads the data on-the-fly from a remote datasource.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    All<O>
    A query which matches all objects in the collection.
    Between<O,A extends Comparable<A>>
    Asserts than an attribute is between a lower and an upper bound.
    Equal<O,A>
    Asserts than an attribute equals a certain value.
    ExistsIn<O,F,A>
    Asserts than an object exists in a foreign collection, based on an attribute in the local collection being equal to an attribute in the foreign collection, and optionally with restrictions applied to objects in the foreign collection.
    GreaterThan<O,A extends Comparable<A>>
    Asserts than an attribute is greater than a lower bound.
    Has<O,A>
    Asserts that an attribute has a value (is not null).
    In<O,A>
    Asserts that an attribute has at least one of the values specified by the In query.
    LessThan<O,A extends Comparable<A>>
    Asserts than an attribute is less than an upper bound.
    None<O>
    A query which matches no objects in the collection.
    SimpleQuery<O,A>
    The superclass of Querys which make assertions on attribute values.
    StringContains<O,A extends CharSequence>
    Asserts than a CharSequence-based attribute ends with a given CharSequence-based suffix.
    StringEndsWith<O,A extends CharSequence>
    Asserts than a CharSequence-based attribute ends with a given CharSequence-based suffix.
    StringIsContainedIn<O,A extends CharSequence>
    Asserts than a CharSequence-based attribute is contained in a given CharSequence-based document.
    StringMatchesRegex<O,A extends CharSequence>
    Asserts that an attribute's value matches a regular expression.
    StringStartsWith<O,A extends CharSequence>
    Asserts than a CharSequence-based attribute starts with a given CharSequence-based prefix.
